{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"28a7acae-8f1b-4336-b9d8-959d1880a8e0","content":"Here's the skip attribute for each framework:\n\n| Framework | Attribute |\n|-----------|-----------|\n| **MSTest** | `[Ignore(\"reason\")]` |\n| **xUnit** | `[Fact(Skip = \"reason\")]` or `[Theory(Skip = \"reason\")]` |\n| **NUnit** | `[Ignore(\"reason\")]` |\n| **TUnit** | `[Skip(\"reason\")]` |\n\n**Examples:**\n\n```csharp\n// MSTest\n[TestMethod]\n[Ignore(\"Blocked by bug #1234\")]\npublic void MyMsTest() { }\n\n// xUnit\n[Fact(Skip = \"Blocked by bug #1234\")]\npublic void MyXunitTest() { }\n\n// NUnit\n[Test]\n[Ignore(\"Blocked by bug #1234\")]\npublic void MyNunitTest() { }\n\n// TUnit\n[Test]\n[Skip(\"Blocked by bug #1234\")]\npublic async Task MyTunitTest() { }\n```\n\nAll four frameworks surface the reason string in test results so you can track why tests were skipped.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"89104950-34f7-42c8-8742-cb13dcacbea5","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about the correct skip/ignore attributes for each test framework. I have a skill that can help with this - the `dotnet-test-frameworks` skill which has reference data for skip annotations across MSTest, xUnit, NUnit, and TUnit.","outputTokens":331,"requestId":"1BC2:2811EE:209A32E:24224B0:6A03D27D"},"id":"2ad8c030-db6f-491f-b54e-1a687dac9415","timestamp":"2026-05-13T01:23:16.148Z","parentId":"e4cbde87-cacb-43d8-83b5-821f86893ec4"}
